# Svelte Patterns

- Use Svelte 4 reactive declarations (`$:`) for derived state — chunks, metrics, and comparison values are all reactive
- Bind form controls directly with `bind:value` and `bind:checked`; avoid manual event handlers where binding works
- Keep all app state in `+page.svelte` — no stores needed for this single-page app
- Use `{#if}`, `{#each}` blocks; do not reach for JS DOM manipulation

## Styling

- Tailwind utility classes only — no `<style>` blocks unless truly unavoidable
- Responsive grid: `grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4` pattern for controls
- Color-coded chunks use inline `style` with HSL: `hsl({hue}, 70%, 85%)` — this is intentional, not a Tailwind bypass

## Events

- Prefer `on:click={() => fn()}` inline handlers for simple calls
- Avoid deprecated `createEventDispatcher` for this single-component app

## Anti-patterns to Avoid

- Do not add TypeScript (`lang="ts"`) — project is plain JS
- Do not split into multiple route pages — keep as single `+page.svelte`
- Do not import external charting/UI libraries — Tailwind + vanilla Svelte only
